This course is an advanced introduction to the study of literature written in Portuguese from Brazil, Portugal, Angola, and Mozambique. We will study a select group of authors and texts that are representative of the modern and contemporary literatures of these Lusophone countries. The course objectives are: 

 the dissemination of knowledge based on canonical and non-canonical literary works from the Portuguese-speaking world; 
 the acquisition of analytical tools for textual interpretation of novels, short stories, and poetry; 
 the expansion and improvement of Portuguese linguistic proficiency, both oral and written; 
 the use the literary text as a tool to better understand the cultures of the Portuguese-speaking world, particularly, social, cultural, and political questions that are germane to these countries, but that may also address universal humanistic concerns.
